.TH "nand_check_ecc_caps" 9 "nand_check_ecc_caps" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nand_check_ecc_caps \- check the sanity of preset ECC settings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nand_check_ecc_caps
.BI "(struct nand_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "const struct nand_ecc_caps *caps "  ","
.BI "int oobavail "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
nand chip info structure
.IP "caps" 12
ECC caps info structure
.IP "oobavail" 12
OOB size that the ECC engine can use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When ECC step size and strength are already set, check if they are supported
by the controller and the calculated ECC bytes fit within the chip's OOB.
On success, the calculated ECC bytes is set.
